{
  "stem": "5810.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When they say that war is over, I don't think it will never be over for Holocaust survivors, and certainly not the hidden children of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You question daily, you wonder why, how could it have happened?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People for 45 years now, before this first hidden children conference, have not let us complain.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we've learned not to complain, to suffer in silence, because we had to do that for three, four years anyway.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had to hold back our grief, and our, our weaknesses, and our crying, all of those things.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was very, almost easy, not to speak out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And for me, because of the fact that it, I guess it saved my life not to be Jewish, and not to sound Jewish, and not to look Jewish, it became very important to me after the war that I was never, never discovered as a Jew, to be pointed out as a Jew, or to be even different than anyone else.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was very, very important to me, at first, in Belgium to speak French without being pointed out as a stranger, and later on when I came to the United States, to learn English in the best way I knew how not to be discovered.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And to this date, I have a problem to, believe it or not, speak in public or being-- or, or have anyone listen in the hopes that they don't point out an accent, or they discover an accent.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I say I, I am not a Jew, I am.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if somebody discovers that I am a Jew or, or because of that ever made an anti-Semitic remark or call me today dirty Jew, certainly I am a Jew again.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
